quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  77,1,By the companies (of angels) sent one after another for some good results
  77,2,And then moving as fast and forcefully as tempests
  77,3,And by those enfolding the Scrolls of Revelation
  77,4,And serving (for right and wrong) to be separated with all clarity
  77,5,And so bringing down the Revelation
  77,6,In order that some may have the means to ask for forgiveness and that some may be warned
  77,7,Surely what you are promised is bound to take place
  77,8,When the stars are effaced
  77,9,And when the sky is rent asunder
  77,10,And when the mountains are blown away (as dust)
  77,11,And when the time for the Messengers (to bear witness for or against their communities) is appointed
  77,12,For what day has the term (of all this) been set
  77,13,For the Day of Judgment and Distinction (between people according to how they believed and acted in the world)
  77,14,What enables you to perceive what the Day of Judgment and Distinction is
  77,15,Woe on that Day to those who deny (the Day)
  77,16,Did We not destroy the ancient peoples (who denied)
  77,17,So do We make the later generations (of the same standing) follow them (in being destroyed)
  77,18,For thus do We deal with the disbelieving criminals
  77,19,Woe on that Day to those who deny
  77,20,(How and why do you dare to deny?) Did We not create you from a humble fluid
  77,21,"Then We placed it in a firm, secure place (to remain)"
  77,22,"For a known, pre-ordained term (of gestation)"
  77,23,"Thus have We determined (everything related to your existence), and how excellent We are in determining"
  77,24,Woe on that Day to those who deny
  77,25,Have We not made the earth a receptacle
  77,26,Both for the living and the dead
  77,27,"And set therein mountains firm, lofty in stature, and given you to drink the sweet water (gushing out of them)"
  77,28,Woe on that Day to those who deny
  77,29,Move towards that (Fire) which you used to deny
  77,30,Move towards the shadow (of black smoke ascending) in three columns
  77,31,It will neither give (cooling) shade nor will it be of any avail against the flame
  77,32,It (the Fire) will throw out sparks like castles
  77,33,(Scattered abroad) as if they were yellow camels
  77,34,Woe on that Day to those who deny
  77,35,This will be a Day when they (the deniers) will not utter a word
  77,36,Nor will they be allowed to offer excuses
  77,37,Woe on that Day to those who deny
  77,38,"This is the Day of Judgment and Distinction (between people, according to how they believed and acted in the world). We have assembled you and the earlier ones (from earlier communities who were also deniers)"
  77,39,"So if you have a scheme (to save yourselves from My punishment), then apply it (against Me)"
  77,40,Woe on that Day to those who deny